mistral.reason: Separate Baptists are still a part of the Christian denomination, they just have distinct practices and beliefs that differentiate them from other Baptist groups. They do not represent a former Christian denomination.

gemma2.reason: The provided text details the historical development and beliefs of Separate Baptists, indicating they are a distinct branch within Baptist Christianity, not a former denomination.

qwen2.5.reason: Separate Baptists are not considered former Christian denominations. They continue to exist as a distinct group within Baptist Christianity, maintaining their own traditions and beliefs while also sharing some similarities with other Baptist groups. Their historical separation from the Church of England and later from other Baptist movements does not classify them as former Christian denominations but rather as an ongoing part of Baptist history and practice.
